Add a new property to the entity in this catalog.

Usage: /add-property <property-name> <type>

Example: /add-property version string
Example: /add-property priority integer
Example: /add-property enabled boolean
Example: /add-property categories array

Read the skill file at .claude/skills/add-property.md and follow ALL steps to:
1. Update catalog.yaml with the new property definition
2. Run catalog-gen generate and make gen/openapi-server
3. Update internal/catalog/providers/yaml_provider.go (struct + mapping)
4. Update internal/db/service/<entity>.go (both mapper functions)
5. Update internal/server/openapi/api_<entity>_service_impl.go (converter)
6. Verify with: go build ./...

IMPORTANT: All 4 editable files must be updated for the property to work end-to-end:
- YAML parsing (yaml_provider.go)
- Database persistence (<entity>.go - map<Entity>ToContextProperties)
- Database retrieval (<entity>.go - mapContextTo<Entity>)
- API response (api_<entity>_service_impl.go - convertToOpenAPIModel)
